# 5) Library Book Management System

## App.java

```java
package com.example;

public class App {

    private int totalBooks = 10;

    public int getTotalBooks() {
        return totalBooks;
    }

    public boolean issueBook() {
        if (totalBooks > 0) {
            totalBooks--;
            return true;
        }
        return false;
    }

    public void returnBook() {
        totalBooks++;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        App library = new App();

        System.out.println("Initial Books: " + library.getTotalBooks());

        boolean issued = library.issueBook();
        System.out.println("Book Issued: " + issued);
        System.out.println("Books After Issue: " + library.getTotalBooks());

        library.returnBook();
        System.out.println("Books After Return: " + library.getTotalBooks());
    }
}
```

## AppTest.java

```java
package com.example;

import org.junit.Test;
import static org.junit.Assert.*;

public class AppTest {

    @Test
    public void testIssueBook() {
        App library = new App();
        boolean result = library.issueBook();
        assertTrue(result);
        assertEquals(9, library.getTotalBooks());
    }

    @Test
    public void testReturnBook() {
        App library = new App();
        library.returnBook();
        assertEquals(11, library.getTotalBooks());
    }

    @Test
    public void testIssueBookUntilEmpty() {
        App library = new App();

        for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
            library.issueBook();
        }

        assertEquals(0, library.getTotalBooks());
        assertFalse(library.issueBook());
    }
}
```

## Output

```text
Initial Books: 10
Book Issued: true
Books After Issue: 9
Books After Return: 10
```

